<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Because" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Because,</orth> by cause, on account; 1) followed by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>this swain, b. of his great limb or joint, shall pass Pompey the Great,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 135</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>they dare not fight with me, b. of the queen my mother,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 1, 21</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) followed by <emph>that</emph>: <cit><quote>b. that I familiarly sometimes do use you for my fool, your sauciness will jest upon my love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 26</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.117" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.96" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 96</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 1, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.52" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 52</bibl>.
<lb />3) without <emph>that,</emph> in the same sense: <bibl n="shak. ven 378" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 378</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 378" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 378</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 378" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 378</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 35" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 42.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 42, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.101.9" default="NO" valid="yes">101, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.102.14" default="NO" valid="yes">102, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 106" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 61</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.173" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.5.60" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 147</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 147</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.84" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.84" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.84" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 84</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 24</bibl> etc. etc.
<lb />4) preceded by <emph>for,</emph> in the same sense: <cit><quote>not for b. your brows are blacker,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 2.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 1, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and why rail I on this commodity? but for b. he hath not woo'd me yet,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.588" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 588</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>and for b. the world is populous, I cannot do it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 3</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="92" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>